HEADWORD: Sirloin
<hw>Sir"loin`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A corruption of
<ets>surloin</ets>. Not so called because this cut of beef was once
jocosely knighted (dubbed Sir Loin) by an English king, as according to
a popular story.]</ety> <def>A loin of beef, or a part of a loin.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>surloin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

